# Configuration for the by-your-command Discord bot.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (init.sh does this for you on first run) and fill in the
# values below. `.env` is git-ignored and must never be committed.

# ── Required ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Your Discord bot token: Developer Portal → your app → Bot → Reset Token.
#
# This bot also needs BOTH privileged intents, enabled under
# Bot → Privileged Gateway Intents in the Developer Portal:
#   • Message Content Intent  — /tfurl reads the text of the message it unfurls
#   • Server Members Intent   — /showmymode edits nicknames and scans members
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=

# ── Optional ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# A single server (guild) ID. When set, slash commands are published to just that
# server and appear instantly. When left blank, commands are published globally,
# which can take up to ~1 hour to show up.
#
# To find it: enable Developer Mode (User Settings → Advanced), then right-click
# your server's icon → Copy Server ID.
DISCORD_GUILD_ID=
